text: {| |} Puyallup (YT‑806) is a United States Navy . The tugboat is named for the people of the Puyallup tribe. ==Construction== The contract for Puyallup was awarded 8 October 2010. She was laid down 1 March 2010 by J.M. Martinac Shipbuilding Corp., Tacoma, Washington and launched 6 November 2010. ==Operational history== Puyallup was delivered to the Navy at Yokosuka and is assigned to Commander Fleet Activities Yokosuka. ==References== * * Category:Valiant-class tugboats Category:Ships built in Tacoma, Washington Category:2011 ships
